4507 ///   icmp eq/ne (x & ~Mask), 0     to    icmp DstPred x, Mask
4508 ///   icmp eq/ne (~x | Mask), -1     to    icmp DstPred x, Mask
4509 /// Where Mask is some pattern that produces all-ones in low bits:
4510 ///    (-1 >> y)
4511 ///    ((-1 << y) >> y)     <- non-canonical, has extra uses
4512 ///   ~(-1 << y)
4513 ///    ((1 << y) + (-1))    <- non-canonical, has extra uses
4514 /// The Mask can be a constant, too.
4515 /// For some predicates, the operands are commutative.
4516 /// For others, x can only be on a specific side.
